  <steps>
    <step num="0">Carefully slice 3 gold potatoes into ⅛ inch (3 mm) slices using a knife or mandoline. </step>
    <step num="1">In a large bowl, coat chips with vinegar so all are submerged, allow to sit for 30 minutes (the longer they sit the more vinegary they will taste). </step>
    <step num="2">Preheat the oven to 350ºF (175ºC). </step>
    <step num="3">Drain the chips and then mix in salt and pepper. </step>
    <step num="4">Arrange chips on greased baking sheet. </step>
    <step num="5">Bake for 30-35 minutes. </step>
    <step num="6">Enjoy! </step>
  </steps>
